    {
      "q": "What PSI should my tires be?",
      "a": "Check the sticker inside your driver's door jamb — not the tire sidewall. Most cars require 30-35 PSI. Adjust for temperature: for every 10°F drop, tire pressure decreases about 1 PSI."
    },
    {
      "q": "Can a portable inflator fix a completely flat tire?",
      "a": "Yes, if the flat is from a slow leak or a nail that's still in the tire. If the tire has a blowout or major sidewall damage, an inflator won't help — you'll need a replacement."
